            <entry xml:id="entry_kʼannæg" xml:lang="os-x-iron">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>kʼannæg</orth></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>маленький</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>small</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>малый</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>short</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Nartæ se ʽmgæron k˳yd waʒync axæm kʼannæǵy?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>как нарты допускают к себе такого маленького?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>how do the Narts admit such a small boy to themselves?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>107</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kʼannæg syvællonæj sax˳yr dæn sæfty x˳ysnægyl</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>малым ребенком приучился я к гибельному воровству</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>as a small child I got accustomed to disastrous theft</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>98</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к иран. %i*kanya-ka%i ‘малый’, ‘юный’. В других
                    иранских языках выступает чаще со значением ‘девушка’, ‘девочка’: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kanīz</w>
                        <gloss><q>девушка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kine</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ZDMG"
                            /><biblScope>XLVII 705</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>kincākā, kintika</w>
                        <gloss><q>девушка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>девочка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>qnčk</w>
                        <gloss><q>дитя</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>knčyk</w>
                        <gloss><q>девочка</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>kanaiska</w>
                        <gloss><q>мизинец</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>kanīk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/>
                        <w>kanīg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kainyā-</w>
                        <gloss><q>девушка</q></gloss></mentioned>. Значение ‘малый’ — в <mentioned
                        xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>kandər</w>
                        <gloss><q>меньший</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"
                            ><w>kandəra</w>
                        <gloss><q>мизинец</q></gloss></mentioned>. — В осетинском употребительна
                    старая форма сравнительной степени <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼaddær"/> (из
                    %i*kan-dær%i, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæddyn"/> из %iband-%i и др.),
                    наряду с новой %ikʼannæg-dær%i. — Для %inn%i из %iny%i ср. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_īnnæ"/> из %ianya-%i. Трудно объяснить появление в начале
                    смычно-гортанного согласного. Оно не подводится ни под какое из известных
                    условий появления в осетинском согласных этого типа (см. <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>518-525</biblScope></bibl>). По всей
                    видимости, здесь имела место контаминация с каким-нибудь субстратным
                    (кавказским) словом; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>k’änk</w>
                        <gloss><q>мальчик</q></gloss></mentioned>. — От этого же корня <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ḱynʒ"/> | %ikinʒæ%i ‘невестка’ (из
                            %i*kan-tī-%i).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                            /><biblScope>II 70</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>37, 47</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope
                            xml:lang="ru">21 сл.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>20, 524</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to Iranian %i*kanya-ka%i ‘small’, ‘young’. In other
                    Iranian languages it is usually used in the meaning ‘girl’, ‘small girl’:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kanīz</w>
                        <gloss><q>girl</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kine</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ZDMG"
                            /><biblScope>XLVII 705</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>kincākā, kintika</w>
                        <gloss><q>girl</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>small girl</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>qnčk</w>
                        <gloss><q>child</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>knčyk</w>
                        <gloss><q>small girl</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>kanaiska</w>
                        <gloss><q>little finger</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>kanīk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/>
                        <w>kanīg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kainyā-</w>
                        <gloss><q>girl</q></gloss></mentioned>. The meaning ‘small’ is attested in
                        <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>kandər</w>
                        <gloss><q>the smallest</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"
                            ><w>kandəra</w>
                        <gloss><q>little finger</q></gloss></mentioned>. — The old comparative form
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼaddær"/> (from %i*kan-dær%i, as <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_bæddyn"/> from %iband-%i etc.) is commonly used in
                    Ossetic, alongside with a new one %ikʼannæg-dær%i. — For %inn%i from %iny%i cf.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īnnæ"/> from %ianya-%i. It is difficult to
                    explain the emergence of guttural obstruent consonant in the beginning of this
                    word. It does not fit under any known conditions of emergence of such consonants
                    in Ossetic (see <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>518-525</biblScope></bibl>). Apparently, there was a
                    contamination with some substate (Caucasian) word; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>k’änk</w>
                        <gloss><q>boy</q></gloss></mentioned>. — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ḱynʒ"
                    /> | %ikinʒæ%i ‘невестка’ (из %i*kan-tī-%i) is from the same root.%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                        70</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>37, 47</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope xml:lang="en">22 ff.</biblScope></bibl> —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>20,
                            524</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
